  {
    "client_msg_id": "7eba7c55-4628-4cda-8a9b-133d69b8359a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "modularity, small pieces with few dependencies does guarantee better results than the tangled mess that is OOP. Compare two large programs, one written in Modula-2 versus Java, and you will see a huge difference. Clarity as to where a computation is being performed, nicely controlled visibility, tons of compile-time and run-time checks that catch stupid errors quickly also add to its advantages. No operator overloading or ambiguity created by too-clever programmers helps. But it is also true that as a system grows its overall complexity to a maintainer also grows.",
    "user": "UEQ6M68H0",
    "ts": "1557021162.157400",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
